**OREKA**

**Master Pronunciation Guide**

*Internal Author Reference — For Testing All Hard Names*

Each published book carries its own pronunciation guide covering names in that book only. This document is the complete master list.

**HOW TO USE THIS GUIDE:**

Phonetics are written in plain English approximations, not IPA. Stressed syllables are in ALL CAPS. "Zh" throughout = the French "j" sound, as in "measure" or "mirage." Soft "th" = as in "the" or "there." Hard "th" = as in "think." Test every name in this list aloud before the book goes to print.

# **PEOPLES AND RACES**

| **Term** | **Pronunciation** | **Category** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Dómnathar | *DOME-nah-thar* | Race/Faction | Accent on first syllable; "th" is soft as in "the" |
| Dómnathar-Zhuan | *DOME-nah-thar ZHOO-ahn* | Place/World | Their home world; "Zh" = French "j" sound |
| Pekakarlik | *PEH-kah-KAR-lik* | Race | Water-aligned dwarves; stress the third syllable |
| Rarozhki | *rah-ROZH-kee* | Race | Fire-aligned dwarves; "zh" = French "j"; stress second syllable |
| Visetri | *VIH-seh-tree* | Race/Faction | Earth-aligned dwarves; three syllables, light stress |
| Na'wasua | *nah-WAH-soo-ah* | Race | Wind-aligned elves; apostrophe = brief pause; four syllables |
| Pasua | *PAH-soo-ah* | Race | Earth-aligned elves; three syllables |
| Hasura | *hah-SOO-rah* | Race | Water-aligned elves; stress second syllable |
| Kovaka | *koh-VAH-kah* | Race | Fire-aligned elves; stress second syllable |
| Mytroan | *MY-troh-an* | Adj. (people) | Adjective form of Mytrone; three syllables |
| Eruskan | *eh-RUS-kan* | Race | Water/Earth humans; stress second syllable |
| Taraf-Imro | *TAR-af IM-roh* | People/Tradition | Fire-aligned humans; two-word name, equal stress |
| Farborn | *FAR-born* | Race | Two syllables; straightforward |
| Indorach | *IN-doh-rahk* | Race/Faction | Domnathar house; hard final k |

# **PLACES AND GEOGRAPHY**

| **Term** | **Pronunciation** | **Category** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Kharazhad | *KAR-ah-ZHAD* | Place | "Zh" = French "j"; stress falls on final syllable |
| Sylaraeth | *SIL-ah-reeth* | Place | Veil city in Twin Rivers; final "th" is soft; rhymes with "wreath" |
| Peravost | *PAIR-ah-vost* | Place | City of Bridges; three syllables; stress first |
| Aldenheim | *AWL-den-hyme* | Place | Fallen fortress city; "heim" rhymes with "time" |
| Myrnaazhul | *MIR-nah-ZHOOL* | Place | "Zh" = French "j"; final syllable rhymes with "cool" |
| Tethzhaar | *TETH-zhahr* | Place/Creature | "Zh" = French "j"; "aa" = elongated "ah" |
| Ssyraeth | *SSIR-ree-eth* | Place/Creature | Initial "Ss" is a drawn-out hiss; soft final "th" |
| Dómnathar-Zhuan | *DOME-nah-thar ZHOO-ahn* | Place | Home world of the Domnathar |
| Highspire | *HY-spire* | Place | Two syllables; straightforward |
| Stoneharbor | *STONE-har-bor* | Place | Three syllables; straightforward |
| Forkmeet | *FORK-meet* | Place | Two syllables; straightforward |
| Lakeshore | *LAKE-shore* | Place | Two syllables; shared between Kinsweave and Tidebloom |
| Lakewell | *LAKE-well* | Place | Two syllables; shared between Kinsweave and Tidebloom |
| Kailian Sea | *KAY-lee-an* | Place | Northern inland sea; stress first syllable |
| Apelian Sea | *ah-PEE-lee-an* | Place | Southern inland sea; stress second syllable |

# **DEITIES AND DIVINE FIGURES**

| **Term** | **Pronunciation** | **Category** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Cinvarin | *SIN-vah-rin* | Deity | First Ascended God; three syllables |
| Hareem | *hah-REEM* | Deity | The Golden Rose; CE; stress second syllable; one "r" |
| Harreem | *SAME AS HAREEM* | INCORRECT | Common misspelling — canonical form is Hareem (one r) |
| Kaile'a | *KAY-leh-ah* | Deity | Apostrophe = slight pause; three syllables |
| Gonmareck | *GON-mah-rek* | Deity | Gunny; hard final k; stress first syllable |
| Semyon | *SEM-yon* | Deity | Two syllables; "y" as in "yes" |
| Tarvek Wen | *TAR-vek WEN* | Deity | Two-word name; Doombringer; equal stress |
| Ludus Galerius | *LOO-dus gah-LEER-ee-us* | Deity | Stone's Hand; Latin-style pronunciation |
| Apela Kelsoe | *ah-PEH-lah KEL-soh* | Deity | Windrider; stress second syllable of each word |
| Durak Stonewatch | *DOO-rahk STONE-watch* | Deity | Judge of Oaths; stress first syllable |

# **FACTIONS, INSTITUTIONS, AND KEY NPCs**

| **Term** | **Pronunciation** | **Category** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Eke Concordant | *EE-kay KON-kor-dant* | Faction/Institution | NOT "Eka Concordance" — canonical spelling |
| Mithril Legion | *MITH-ril LEE-jun* | Faction | Visetri wandering brotherhood; "Mithril" = standard fantasy |
| Taraf-Imro | *TAR-af IM-roh* | Faction/Tradition | Fire-human bardic tradition; also a people |
| Stone Covenant | *STONE KUV-eh-nant* | Faction | NOT "Stone Concordant" — canonical name |
| Karveth Stonefire | *KAR-veth STONE-fire* | NPC | High Thane of Kharazhad |
| Agama Stonefire | *ah-GAH-mah STONE-fire* | NPC | Forgekeeper; Karveth's son |

# **MECHANICS AND SETTING TERMS**

| **Term** | **Pronunciation** | **Category** | **Notes** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Kin-sense | *KIN-sense* | Mechanic | Two words hyphenated; elemental resonance detection |
| Abyssal Silence | *ah-BIS-al SY-lens* | Mechanic | Domnathar Kin-sense non-registration effect |
| False Silence | *FAWLS SY-lens* | Mechanic | Personal Deceiver cloak; distinct from Abyssal Silence |
| Deceiver's Feat | *deh-SEE-verz FEET* | Mechanic | Ability to mask Kin-sense registration; personal use only |
| Thalorien | *tha-LOR-ee-en* | Term | Four syllables; stress second |
| Apotheosis | *ah-poth-ee-OH-sis* | Term | Standard English pronunciation; stress third syllable |
| Magi | *MAH-jee* | Class/Tradition | Oreka's oldest spellcasting tradition; not MAY-jy |
| Summer Lands | *SUM-er LANDZ* | Term | Universal Kin term for the Spirit Realm |
| Vael'domin | *VAY-el DOH-min* | Term | Apostrophe = brief pause between syllables |
| Velathenor | *veh-LATH-eh-nor* | Term | Soft "th"; four syllables; stress second |

# **NOTES FOR INDIVIDUAL BOOK GUIDES**

## **Player Handbook**

Include: all Peoples and Races entries, all Deities entries, all Mechanics and Setting Terms entries, Kharazhad, Eke Concordant, Stone Covenant, Mithril Legion, Taraf-Imro.

## **Dungeon Master****'****s Guide**

Include: all entries. The DMG guide is the most complete per-book version. Add any NPC names specific to the seven regions.

## **Monster Manual**

Include: Domnathar, Domnathar-Zhuan, Tethzhaar, Ssyraeth, Myrnaazhul, Kin-sense, Abyssal Silence, False Silence, Breach, Summer Lands, and any creature-specific names. Creature entries should carry the pronunciation in the creature name header line, not in a separate appendix.